snippet: Investigators matched DNA from a chain used in an Occupy Wall St. protest to DNA linked to the 2004 killing of Sarah Fox, a Juilliard student.
abstract: DNA recovered from a chain used at the site of an Occupy Wall Street protest in March is linked to the unsolved killing of Juilliard student Sarah Fox in 2004; police investigators are seeking to determine the significance of the discovery, noting that the match may not necessarily lead to the identification of Fox's killer.

byline.original: By WILLIAM K. RASHBAUM and WENDY RUDERMAN

lead_paragraph: Investigators matched DNA from a chain used in an Occupy Wall St. protest to DNA linked to the 2004 killing of Sarah Fox, a Juilliard student.

headline.seo: DNA at Occupy Wall Street Protest Site Said to Be Tied to Sarah Fox Killing
headline.main: DNA Said to Link Occupy Wall St. Protest and 2004 Killing
headline.print_headline: DNA at Protest Scene Is Said To Be Linked to 2004 Killing
